result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael A Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Per Order of Presiding Judge, Felony Division, this request/motion is hereby assigned to the Hon. J.D. Watts, Br. 15, calendar successor, for review. mag
Defendant's pro se motion for good time credit.

Defendant Michael A Jones in court with attorney Virginia M. Stuller.  Nathaniel Emery Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Clerk;ds

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements by counsel and defendant.  COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, must provide a DNA specimen for testing and pay the DNA surcharge and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

Count 1:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 36 months with 14 days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 18 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 18 months.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of 3 years.

Count 2:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 36 months; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 18 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 18 months - consecutive to Count 1.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of 3 years - concurrent.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  1) no violations of the criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) do not use or possess any illegally controlled substances; 3) random screening; 4) AODA, treatment or programs; 5) pay costs, assessments and surcharges or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant; 7) SERVE 12 MONTHS at the House of Correction with work release for work for AODA treatment or counseling - STAYED while actively in the Genesis Residential Treatment program.

Court advises the defendant possession or use of any illegally controlled substance or alcohol forfeits the release privileges.   

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) seek and maintain employment; 3) treatment or programs as recommended; 4) do not use or possess illegally controlled substances; 5) random screening;

Court finds defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program on Count 2 only.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a specimen for DNA testing and pay the surcharge - if not already done.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
Justice Point report received and filed./ds

Court amends bail to $700 cash bail, $200 previously posted, $500 due.  Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  Defendant to be monitored by drug testing.  OR
If an inpatient bed becomes available at Genesis Detox Center cash bail will revert to a $500 signature bond so defendant may report for treatment.
